  "text": "Randall and Tetali [CITATION_1] were the first to combine Diaconis and Saloff-Coste's inequalities with the inequalities relating eigenvalues to mixing times to derive a relationship between the mixing times of two chains. Their result [CITATION_2] Proposition 4] applies to two ergodic reversible chains M and M ′ provided the eigenvalues satisfy certain restrictions (see the remarks following Theorem 10 below).",
